Respect column format by default; add "Override column format" toggle

The card no longer discards the model's format string. By default it now uses
each measure's own format (thousands separator, currency, decimals, custom
formats all carry over). The visual's own thousands-separator / decimals /
display-units settings apply only when the new "Override column format" toggle
is enabled (Actual and Comparison cards). Comparison rows now format with each
comparison column's own format string instead of the Actual column's.

